# Git commit attribution (cloud + agent)

When committing in this repository:

1. **Never** add `Co-authored-by:`, `Made-with: Cursor`, or any Cursor/agent attribution trailer to commit messages.
2. **Before** `git commit`, run `bash scripts/git/disable-cursor-commit-attribution.sh` if hooks may have been reset.
3. **Prefer** `bash scripts/git/commit-clean.sh -m "type(scope): summary"` when Cursor keeps injecting trailers (uses `git commit-tree`, bypasses hooks).
4. Use only approved author identity: `cyre <diazMelgarejo@gmail.com>` (or `Lawrence@cyre.me` / `Codex <codex@openai.com>` per `scripts/git/check_identity.sh`).
5. Multi-repo stack: run `bash scripts/git/apply-attribution-guard-all-repos.sh` after clone or cloud VM boot.

Desktop (optional): Cursor Settings → Agents → Attribution → OFF (IDE/CLI only; cloud may still inject until guards run).
